  "commentary": "With SPX at 7116 sitting right at the max negative gamma strike of 7115, dealers are actively buying the dip here as they're short gamma at this level. The strong positive gamma walls at 7100 (+5.3B), 7130 (+4.2B), and 7150 (+6.8B) create a supportive floor, while the massive 7200 wall (+8.3B) acts as upside resistance where dealers will aggressively sell any rallies. In this PIN regime with total GEX at 65B, expect strong mean reversion dynamics with buyers stepping in on weakness toward 7100 and sellers capping moves toward 7150-7200.\n\nKey levels: 7100 support, 7150-7200 resistance zone, and watch for any break below the 6873 flip strike which would shift the regime bearish.\n\nBottom line: expect a bounce from current levels with upside capped near 7150-7200.",
